      <title>亚洲寻求购买更多美国化石燃料以取悦特朗普</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-20/asia-looks-to-buy-more-us-fossil-fuels-to-make-trump-happy</link>
      <description><![CDATA[为了安抚即将上任的美国总统唐纳德·特朗普，亚洲化石燃料买家得出了同样的结论：购买更多美国石油和天然气。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-20/asia-looks-to-buy-more-us-fossil-fuels-to-make-trump-happy</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 20 Jan 2025 02:02:05 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普称就职前夕集会将结束“美国衰落”</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/trump-tells-inauguration-eve-rally-american-decline-to-end</link>
      <description><![CDATA[当选总统唐纳德·特朗普周日在其第二次就职典礼前夕在华盛顿市中心的首都一号体育馆举行集会，庆祝其就职典礼，随后在几个街区之外举行了一场正式晚宴，出席嘉宾包括特朗普最大的金融支持者和政治盟友，以及寻求接近权力的商业巨头。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/trump-tells-inauguration-eve-rally-american-decline-to-end</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 19 Jan 2025 22:32:57 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>中国面临特朗普回归，出口依存度飙升</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/china-faces-trump-s-return-just-as-reliance-on-exports-soars</link>
      <description><![CDATA[中国正面临唐纳德·特朗普第一任总统任期内重演的紧张和不确定性，但经济却比第一次与美国爆发贸易战时更加疲软，对出口的依赖程度也更高。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/china-faces-trump-s-return-just-as-reliance-on-exports-soars</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 19 Jan 2025 22:00:01 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>TikTok 回归引发对特朗普影响力和北京立场的审视</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/trump-pleases-tiktok-users-but-delay-on-app-s-ban-faces-scrutiny</link>
      <description><![CDATA[唐纳德·特朗普承诺推迟执行威胁禁止 TikTok 的国家安全法。但尚不清楚该应用的中国母公司是否能够或愿意及时获得美国支持者，以避免永久关闭。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/trump-pleases-tiktok-users-but-delay-on-app-s-ban-faces-scrutiny</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 19 Jan 2025 21:59:11 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>美国总统如何行使强大的赦免权</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/presidential-pardons-how-us-leaders-use-their-mighty-clemency-powers</link>
      <description><![CDATA[美国总统的赦免权是宪法中最绝对、最容易被误解的条款之一。正如亚历山大·汉密尔顿所写，赦免权源于公元七世纪英国国王的“赦免特权”，开国元勋们希望拥有强有力的赦免权，以便司法系统“轻松获得有利于不幸有罪的例外”。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-19/presidential-pardons-how-us-leaders-use-their-mighty-clemency-powers</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 19 Jan 2025 17:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
